written by Jiayi Wang 2025.5
This is a directory to inversely determine interaction energies in a canonical ensemble from cross-linking data

run_muCalc.slurm: slurm submission file
run_muCalc_Int.sh: bash file to excute everything in order and collect results to their corresponding folders. 

contact_exp.txt: interaction frequency inferred from total counts of cross linking events
new_Int.txt: input interaction energies(typically start from 0s)

coeff.sh: read the innitial interaction energy and write it into lammps input format to be included in the lammps input file
in.xlms_toy.bak: lammps input back up file, will be re-written to in.xlms_toy for the simulation in each iteration
create_input_for_ContactN.sh: read from the lammps trajectory and prepare input information for analysis in matlab
ContactN.m: matlab file to calculate the contact frequencies between subunits from the current trajectory
new_Int.m: matlab file to update the interaction energies based on the contact frequencies in the current iteration

iteration, lammps_log, lammps_traj are folders to collect simulation and analysis results.
